{{External|rs|rsc=Elemental Staff}}
'''Elemental staves''' provide an unlimited amount of one of the basic elemental [[runes]] ([[air rune|air]], [[water rune|water]], [[earth rune|earth]], and [[fire rune|fire]]) or a combination rune ([[Lava rune|lava]], [[Mud rune|mud]], [[Steam rune|steam]], [[Smoke rune|smoke]], [[Mist rune|mist]], and [[Dust rune|dust]]) and the [[autocast]] option when equipped. The staves come in three different types:
*'''Basic''' elemental staves have no requirements to wield. They can be obtained from various sources, including several [[Staff shops|shops]].
*'''[[Battlestaves]]''' require 30 [[Magic]] and [[Attack]] to wield. They can be obtained from various sources, such as [[Zaff's Superior Staffs!]] (after completing the quest [[What Lies Below]]), and also created by players with the [[Crafting]] skill. Battlestaves that provide combination runes cannot be created by players and are only obtainable through trading or monster drops.
*[[Mystic staves|'''Mystic staves''']] require 40 [[Magic]] and [[Attack]] to wield. They can be created by paying [[Thormac]] 40,000 [[coins]] and giving him a charged battlestaff of the type the player wants (after completing the quest [[Scorpion Catcher]]). They can also be obtained through trading or monster drops.

